<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-20T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-20T20:00:00-05:00" n="641" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d641">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5431/263a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-20T20:00:00-05:00">November 20, 1935—8
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>77. No word has been received regarding requirements set forth in the
                                Department’s 66, October 23, 2 p.m. We are wondering why, since
                                enough time has elapsed for the Swiss to have studied our proposed
                                concessions and requests.</p>
                            <p>Suggest that you endeavor to ascertain from Stucki causes for
                                delay.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>